example.description:
Evaluation of probability of termination for a program adapted from an example due to B. Ycart, parameterized by a function K of type nat→ nat and a natural number N.
        let rec ycart n = if random N < K n then n else ycart (n+1)
        Probability of termination of (ycart n) is shown to be equal to ∏k=n∞ (1−F k), with F n=K n/(1+N).
